{{Exam-question|Exam Code=CT1 S2015|Number=3|Part=i|Marks=2}}
Annuity duration = (Ia)/a = 56.63280290 / (9.76047671 / 1.04) = 6.0 years.
<fin-math><parameters><request>get_annuity_increasing</request><m>1</m><i_effective>0.04</i_effective><term>12</term><value/><increasing>1</increasing></parameters></fin-math>
{{Exam-question|Exam Code=CT1 S2015|Number=3|Part=ii|Marks=3}}
For bond, effective interest rate = i(2)/2 = 0.03960781 / 2 = 0.0198039 per half year.
<fin-math><parameters><request>get_interest</request><m>2</m><source_m/><source_rate/><i_effective>0.04</i_effective></parameters></fin-math>
Bond duration in half years \begin{align} & = \frac{5/2\ (Ia)_\require{enclose}{\enclose{actuarial}{2 \times 8}} + 100 \times 2 \times 8 v^{(2 * 8)}}{5/2 \ a_\require{enclose}{\enclose{actuarial}{2 \times 8}} + 100 v^{(2 \times 8)}} \\ & = \frac{2.50 \times 109.93242001 + 100 \times 16 \times 1.04^8 }{2.50 \times 13.86813443 / 1.0198039 + 100 \times 1.04^8} \\ & = 14.42 \mbox{ half-years}. \end{align}
Bond duration in years = 14.42/2 = 7.2 years.
<fin-math><parameters><request>get_annuity_increasing</request><m>1</m><i_effective>0.0198039</i_effective><term>16</term><value/><increasing>1</increasing></parameters></fin-math>

